25/01/2008
MELBOURNE, Australia -- Serbia's Novak Djokovic beat defending champion Roger Federer in straight sets on Friday (January 25th) to reach the finals of the Australian Open. 
The stunning upset means Djokovic, the number 3 seed, will face unseeded Jo-Wilfried Tsonga of France on Sunday. 
Federer, ranked number one in the world, had been cruising to his third straight win at the Open, until Djokovic derailed him. 
(BBC, AP - 25/01/08)
